title: DIY Lasercut Christmas Tree
description:
This is a lasercut christmas tree model. The entire project is made from cheap 0.200" plywood you can buy at a hardware store (no extra dowels or anything) so it's really easy to cut out and assemble! Hope you enjoy!

Part files:
- .dxf, .pdf, and .ai
- https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2682743

Materials:
- 0.200" plywood (I used cheap underlayment)
- Glue (wood glue or superglue)
- Spray polyurethane
- Scratch remover/stain or permanent marker

Tools:
- laser cutter (preferably at least 40W)
- files/sandpaper
